        "text": "\"Strange World\" was supposed to be the big family film for the Christmas season. The animated film is said to have cost around 180 million dollars, plus marketing costs. However, #StrangeWorld flopped more than any other film by the #Disney company in the past ten years. The company is in a deep crisis - #Lightyear already flopped and we'd rather not even talk about \"Pinocchio\" on Disneyplus. Now even former CEO Bob Iger will return to lead the company for another two years. But why did \"Strange World\" fail so badly at the box office? The real reason lies in the narrative - yes, Disney has attempted to produce an anti-Disney film with \"Strange World\". However, this goes down badly with the usual target groups. But even beyond that, it is questionable whether this new dramaturgy can really work. More on this by Wolfgang M. Schmitt in the film analysis.\n \n\n "
